      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JIGSAW (1) comes back from a successful NZ trip having won the G1 Railway Stakes at Ellerslie when last seen. He's found a rich vein of form of late, winner of his past four, and you could argue all were against better opposition than he finds here. To counter that, he is off 7 weeks and has 61kg, but he finds a fairly easy lead and he may just be too talented for them. NDOLA (4) is the 'weights' horse, dropping 5kg from a win at Flemington. He was strongest late there, but staying at 1200m and back around a bend is a slight niggle. SHE'S BULLETPROOF (2) was just fair first up in the G1 Oakleigh Plate, a race she ran second in last year. Not sure she's going that well but on her day she'd give it an almighty shake. RAIKOKE (8) would need clear new peaks to be challenging the top few but is best of the rest.",
